caption: So I ordered Tostones, Maduros, carne Frita and chicharron de pollo. After waiting an hour, which is understandable, my food arrives. Maduros missing.  I call back. 30 minutes later still don’t arrive. My tostones getting cold and so are my meats as I wait for the order.  Ruined the entire meal. Cold tostones suck. Wanted everything fresh and hot, together.  They should have replaced the entire meal. Take the cold food back.  I should’ve ordered Chinese.  *hour later no Maduros. Soggy tostones and they say they’re busy, it’s not their fault.
Best food in East New York

Great authentic Dominican food for a decent price! The portions were huge! I have tried their fried chicken chunks (chicharrones de pollo) and they're flavorful, perfect amount of salt and fried perfectly. My brother got the pernil and it was a bit dry but very flavorful. Their mofongo was also very tasty.

When food, art and pleasure are indistinguishable from each other, you are elevated to a dining experience that's beyond reality. Alinea deserves every single one of those 3 Michelin stars. It's an experience, a celebration of culinary excellence and creativity. 14 courses, each with a theme of their own spread across 3 hours replete with presentations and a trip to the kitchen.

The food here is always great, I pick up the staples before going by my grandparents. It's got a home cooked feel for sure. I typically go with white rice, beans, rotisserie chicken, pork shoulder, and sweet plantains.  They may have a paella which is also really good.  It can be a little slow to get everything together, but it's still worth the visit. I'll certainly be back again.
